cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with few-shot image classification, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture for few-shot learning, which involves measuring the relations between query images and support classes, indicating that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using a task-aware Contrastive Measure Strategy, which could suggest it belongs to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on popular image datasets, indicating it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
